🤖 LangChain Q&A Chatbot

An AI-powered Question & Answer chatbot built using LangChain, OpenAI
GPT models, and Streamlit. This application provides real-time,
intelligent responses through a simple web interface and demonstrates
seamless integration of Large Language Models (LLMs) into interactive
applications.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

🚀 Features

-   Real-time AI-generated responses using OpenAI GPT
-   Interactive web interface with Streamlit
-   Secure API key management using .env
-   Lightweight and modular architecture
-   Easily extendable for conversational AI, RAG, or voice agents

------------------------------------------------------------------------

🛠️ Tech Stack

-   Language: Python
-   Framework: LangChain
-   LLM: OpenAI GPT-4o-mini
-   Frontend: Streamlit
-   Config: Python-dotenv

------------------------------------------------------------------------

📂 Project Structure

langchain-qa-chatbot/ │ ├── app.py ├── requirements.txt ├── .env └──
README.md

------------------------------------------------------------------------

⚙️ Setup Instructions

1.  Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/saznashaik/langchain.git cd langchain

2.  Create virtual environment

python -m venv venv venv# Windows

3.  Install dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

4.  Add OpenAI API key in .env

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

5.  Run the application

streamlit run app.py

------------------------------------------------------------------------

🧠 How It Works

1.  User enters a question in the Streamlit interface
2.  LangChain sends the query to OpenAI GPT model
3.  Model generates an intelligent response
4.  Response is displayed instantly to the user

------------------------------------------------------------------------

🎯 Use Cases

-   AI Chatbots
-   Educational Assistants
-   Customer Support Automation
-   GenAI Learning and Portfolio Projects

------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔒 Security Note

Ensure .env is added to .gitignore to protect API keys.

